            <h1>  API Integration
</h1>
              <p class="lead">Twitter has a diverse developer community that uses our API to create all sorts of neat applications.</p>
  <p>While an advanced feature, our API allows you to take advantage of Twitter's robust features, and can help you create a richer consumer experience. For instance, using the Tweet Button allows people to Tweet what they are interested in when they come across it on your site.</p>
  <a href="https://dev.twitter.com"><img alt="dev.twitter.com" class="bordered" src="/a/1314118012/images/business/dev.twitter.com.jpg" /></a>
  <p>If your business is interested in using our API in your website or application, please <a href="https://dev.twitter.com">visit our developer website</a>, which hosts all our documentation, the API status and links to discussion forums, for more information.</p>

              <a class="btn btn-m btn-blue" href="/en/advertise/start">Next: Start Advertising &rarr;</a>

